        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I get internal server error when try to execute query via Zend_Db_Adapter_Pdo_Mysql\r\n\r\n$db = new Zend_Db_Adapter_Pdo_Mysql($config);\r\n$stmt = $db->query($sql);\r\n\r\nif my $sql string is relatively small it works fine.\r\nbut if $sql strin length is for example 36194 characters i get this weird \"Internal server error\" code 500\r\n\r\nI checked it using plain PDO syntax and it worked fine so this pure Zend problem.\r\nIt looks like problem is in Zend_Db_Statement_Pdo.   "
